Commentary Text: Shankar to Pant, out Lalit Yadav Run Out!! A tragic way to end the partnership for DC! Was worked away into the leg-side and they went for the second run but not with conviction. Lalit Yadav was always struggling, and Manohar's throw at the bowler's end is pinpoint, catching the batter short. The twist though, was that one bail had gone off early due to Shankar's foot being in contact with the stumps. However, the other bail was on and he dislodged it. If both bails had gone off, he would have had to rip the stump out. That was what Pant was confused about, Lalit Yadav too didn't walk off and eventually has to after the umps inform the duo. Handy knock from Lalit Yadav but he'll be gutted to get out this way. Lalit Yadav run out (Abhinav Manohar/Shankar) 25(22) [4s-2 6s-1]
